HEADWORD: checkout
<hw>checkout</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the latest time for
vacating a hotel room without being charged for extra time; <as>as, the
<ex>checkout</ex> here is 12 noon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> checkout time.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A counter in a supermarket or other retail store
where one pays for one's purchases.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> checkout counter.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>checkout counter</ent>⟦br⟧
